#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:2
msgid "HTTP 请求走私"
msgstr "HTTP Request Smuggling"

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:5
msgid "简介"
msgstr "Overview"

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:6
msgid ""
"HTTP请求走私是一种干扰网站处理HTTP请求序列方式的技术，最早在 2005 年的一篇 `文章 "
"<https://www.cgisecurity.com/lib/HTTP-Request-Smuggling.pdf>`_ 中被提出。"
msgstr ""
"HTTP request smuggling is a technique that interferes with how a website "
"processes sequences of HTTP requests. It was first proposed in a 2005 `paper"
" <https://www.cgisecurity.com/lib/HTTP-Request-Smuggling.pdf>`_."

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:9
msgid "成因"
msgstr "Root Cause"

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:10
msgid ""
"请求走私大多发生于前端服务器和后端服务器对客户端传入的数据理解不一致的情况。这是因为HTTP规范提供了两种不同的方法来指定请求的结束位置，即 "
"``Content-Length`` 和 ``Transfer-Encoding`` 标头。"
msgstr ""
"Request smuggling usually occurs when frontend and backend servers interpret"
" client-supplied data differently. This is because the HTTP specification "
"provides two different ways to specify where a request ends: the ``Content-"
"Length`` and ``Transfer-Encoding`` headers."

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:13
msgid "分类"
msgstr "Classification"

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:14
msgid "CLTE：前端服务器使用 ``Content-Length`` 头，后端服务器使用 ``Transfer-Encoding`` 头"
msgstr ""
"CLTE: the frontend server uses the ``Content-Length`` header, while the "
"backend server uses the ``Transfer-Encoding`` header."

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:15
msgid "TECL：前端服务器使用 ``Transfer-Encoding`` 标头，后端服务器使用 ``Content-Length`` 标头。"
msgstr ""
"TECL: the frontend server uses the ``Transfer-Encoding`` header, while the "
"backend server uses the ``Content-Length`` header."

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:16
msgid "TETE：前端和后端服务器都支持 ``Transfer-Encoding`` 标头，但是可以通过以某种方式来诱导其中一个服务器不处理它。"
msgstr ""
"TETE: both the frontend and backend servers support the ``Transfer-"
"Encoding`` header, but one server can be induced in some way not to process "
"it."

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:19
msgid "攻击"
msgstr "Attacks"

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:22
msgid "CL不为0的GET请求"
msgstr "GET Requests with Non-Zero CL"

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:23
msgid ""
"当前端服务器允许GET请求携带请求体，而后端服务器不允许GET请求携带请求体，它会直接忽略掉GET请求中的 ``Content-Length`` "
"头，不进行处理。例如下面这个例子："
msgstr ""
"When the frontend server allows GET requests to carry a request body but the"
" backend server does not, the backend directly ignores the ``Content-"
"Length`` header in the GET request. For example:"

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:35
msgid ""
"前端服务器处理了 ``Content-Length`` ，而后端服务器没有处理 ``Content-Length`` "
"，基于pipeline机制认为这是两个独立的请求，就造成了漏洞的发生。"
msgstr ""
"The frontend server processes ``Content-Length``, while the backend server "
"does not. Based on the pipeline mechanism, the backend treats the data as "
"two independent requests, causing the vulnerability."

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:38
msgid "CL-CL"
msgstr "CL-CL"

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:39
