msgid "这个例子中a就会被带入下一个请求，变为 ``aGET / HTTP/1.1\\r\\n`` 。"
msgstr ""
"In this example, ``a`` is carried into the next request, becoming ``aGET / "
"HTTP/1.1\\r\\n``."

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:54
msgid "CL-TE"
msgstr "CL-TE"

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:55
msgid ""
"CL-TE指前端服务器处理 ``Content-Length`` 这一请求头，而后端服务器遵守RFC2616的规定，忽略掉 ``Content-"
"Length`` ，处理 ``Transfer-Encoding`` 。例如："
msgstr ""
"CL-TE means the frontend server processes the ``Content-Length`` request "
"header, while the backend server follows RFC 2616, ignores ``Content-"
"Length``, and processes ``Transfer-Encoding``. For example:"

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:70
msgid "这个例子中a同样会被带入下一个请求，变为 ``aGET / HTTP/1.1\\r\\n`` 。"
msgstr ""
"In this example, ``a`` is also carried into the next request, becoming "
"``aGET / HTTP/1.1\\r\\n``."

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:73
msgid "TE-CL"
msgstr "TE-CL"

#: ../../source/vuln/httpSmuggling.rst:74
